                            <comment id="13640222" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 08:30:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s definitively not unreasonable. Initially, isRunning was set first so we don&apos;t start the server twice if the &lt;tt&gt;start()&lt;/tt&gt; method was called twice. But tbh it&apos;s not really useful a protection so attaching a trivial patch that just move setting isRunning once the server is indeed started.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
